hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Gap equation in mean‐field:
$$M=-G\sum_{k=1}^N\langle\bar\psi_k\psi_k\rangle.$$

2. One‐loop condensate in Euclidean space ($p_E^2\le\Lambda^2$):
$$\langle\bar\psi_k\psi_k\rangle
=-\int^{\Lambda}\frac{d^2p_E}{(2\pi)^2}\Tr\frac{1}{i\slashed p_E+M}
=-2M\int^{\Lambda}\frac{d^2p_E}{(2\pi)^2}\frac{1}{p_E^2+M^2}.$$

3. Sum over $N$ species:
$$\sum_{k=1}^N\langle\bar\psi_k\psi_k\rangle
=-2NM\int_0^\Lambda\frac{2\pi p\,dp}{(2\pi)^2}\frac{1}{p^2+M^2}
=-\frac{NM}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\Lambda^2+M^2}{M^2}.$$

4. Plug into gap eq. ($M\neq0$):
$$M=G\,\frac{NM}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\Lambda^2+M^2}{M^2}
\;\Rightarrow\;1=\frac{G\,N}{2\pi}\ln\frac{\Lambda^2+M^2}{M^2}.$$

5. Solve for $M$:
$$\ln\frac{\Lambda^2+M^2}{M^2}=\frac{2\pi}{G\,N}
\;\Rightarrow\;\frac{\Lambda^2+M^2}{M^2}
=e^{\frac{2\pi}{G\,N}}
\;\Rightarrow\;M^2=\frac{\Lambda^2}{e^{\frac{2\pi}{G\,N}}-1}.$$
Hence
$$M=\frac{\Lambda}{\sqrt{\exp\!\bigl(\tfrac{2\pi}{G\,N}\bigr)-1}},\quad N=N_cN_f.$$
